<scope ilk="blob" lang="PHP" name="hello.php" src="/private/var/www/paperless/wp-content/old-plugins/hello.php"><scope doc="Plugin Name: Hello Dolly&#10;Plugin URI: http://wordpress.org/extend/plugins/hello-dolly/&#10;Description: This is not just a plugin, it symbolizes the hope and enthusiasm of an entire generation summed up in two words sung most famously by Louis Armstrong: Hello, Dolly. When activated you will randomly see a lyric from &lt;cite&gt;Hello, Dolly&lt;/cite&gt; in the upper right of your admin screen on every page.&#10;Author: Matt Mullenweg&#10;Version: 1.6&#10;Author URI: http://ma.tt/" ilk="function" line="15" lineend="51" name="hello_dolly_get_lyric" returns="wptexturize()" signature="hello_dolly_get_lyric()"><variable citdl="string" line="44" name="lyrics" /></scope><scope doc="This just echoes the chosen line, we'll position it later" ilk="function" line="54" lineend="57" name="hello_dolly" signature="hello_dolly()"><variable citdl="hello_dolly_get_lyric()" line="55" name="chosen" /></scope><scope doc="We need some CSS to position the paragraph" ilk="function" line="63" lineend="78" name="dolly_css" signature="dolly_css()"><variable citdl="is_rtl()" line="65" name="x" /></scope></scope>